Yes... it is basically a Python library for computational fluid dynamics... here's the link... the download is MUCH smaller than ANSYS (which brings a TON of engineering software with it), so we can probably just install on the fly, but feel free to give it a go... here's the Daedalus Project website where they tell you how to install it on a Mac... you probably want to skim though the whole thing first since Daedalus has this annoying habit of telling you how to do things the hard way, only to tell you that there is an installer that you can just run later... <https://dedalus-project.readthedocs.io/en/latest/machines/mac_os/mac_os.html>
